James Boase, landlord of Coppa Dolla pub in Devon, claimed he went to bed at 12.30am and awoke beside his car which had been involved in a car crash .
The 36-year-old claimed he was 'sleepwalking' and was not drunk .
But prosecutors insisted he had failed to stop after hitting another car .
Boase has been remanded on unconditional bail until May 12 for a pre-sentence report .